  "title": "AI/ML Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Design and implement machine learning models for predictive analytics and decision support.</li></ul><ul><li>Conduct data preprocessing, feature engineering, and model training at scale.</li></ul><ul><li>Develop pipelines for continuous learning and model deployment.</li></ul><ul><li>Collaborate with product and engineering teams to integrate AI solutions into applications.</li></ul><ul><li>Monitor model performance, retrain, and optimize algorithms for accuracy and efficiency.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Strong background in machine learning, deep learning, and statistical modeling.</li></ul><ul><li>Proficiency in ML frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch, Scikit-learn).</li></ul><ul><li>Experience with large-scale data processing and distributed training.</li></ul><ul><li>Solid understanding of algorithms, optimization, and applied mathematics.</li></ul><ul><li>Ability to translate business problems into ML solutions with measurable impact.</li></ul>",
